VoiceOver if you have never done

00:00:56.196 --> 00:00:59.636 A:middle
it before and also how VoiceOver

00:01:00.616 --> 00:01:03.286 A:middle
benefits your app.

00:01:05.036 --> 00:01:06.626 A:middle
So what is VoiceOver?

00:01:07.696 --> 00:01:09.796 A:middle
I get some common answers like

00:01:10.616 --> 00:01:12.006 A:middle
well VoiceOver is a screen

00:01:12.006 --> 00:01:12.296 A:middle
reader.

00:01:12.606 --> 00:01:14.906 A:middle
That's true, but VoiceOver

00:01:14.906 --> 00:01:17.716 A:middle
doesn't just read the screen, or

00:01:18.876 --> 00:01:20.236 A:middle
VoiceOver is for the visually

00:01:20.236 --> 00:01:20.676 A:middle
impaired.

00:01:21.276 --> 00:01:24.756 A:middle
It's true, but it's not just for

00:01:24.756 --> 00:01:25.566 A:middle
the visually impaired.

00:01:27.196 --> 00:01:32.226 A:middle
So if VoiceOver is not just for

00:01:32.226 --> 00:01:34.426 A:middle
the visually impaired, and it's

00:01:34.426 --> 00:01:36.646 A:middle
not just a screen reader, what

00:01:36.646 --> 00:01:38.246 A:middle
is it?

00:01:38.976 --> 00:01:40.926 A:middle
VoiceOver is an alternative way

00:01:40.926 --> 00:01:43.826 A:middle
of using you app, and it uses

00:01:43.826 --> 00:01:46.156 A:middle
gestures, a keyboard, or a

00:01:46.156 --> 00:01:48.446 A:middle
Braille display to give a

00:01:48.446 --> 00:01:51.196 A:middle
variety of users equal access to

00:01:51.196 --> 00:01:54.016 A:middle
your experience, and it's built

00:01:54.016 --> 00:01:56.276 A:middle
in to every Apple device.

00:01:56.786 --> 00:01:59.796 A:middle
Now think about that last point.

00:02:00.506 --> 00:02:01.756 A:middle
It's kind of awesome.

00:02:03.046 --> 00:02:05.876 A:middle
I mean that means that every

00:02:05.876 --> 00:02:08.406 A:middle
person who uses your app has

00:02:08.406 --> 00:02:09.515 A:middle
access to VoiceOver.

00:02:11.216 --> 00:02:15.276 A:middle
But not every VoiceOver user has

00:02:15.276 --> 00:02:17.016 A:middle
access to every app.

00:02:17.686 --> 00:02:19.556 A:middle
And that's why you're here.

00:02:20.246 --> 00:02:21.936 A:middle
That's why you are such an

00:02:21.936 --> 00:02:24.026 A:middle
important role in this story

00:02:25.336 --> 00:02:27.496 A:middle
because you must update your app

00:02:28.956 --> 00:02:30.326 A:middle
for us to take advantage of

00:02:30.326 --> 00:02:30.906 A:middle
VoiceOver.

00:02:32.936 --> 00:02:34.516 A:middle
Now when I say updating your app

00:02:34.596 --> 00:02:36.046 A:middle
or supporting VoiceOver, I'm not

00:02:36.046 --> 00:02:37.636 A:middle
talking about creating or

00:02:37.636 --> 00:02:40.286 A:middle
maintaining a alternative or

00:02:40.566 --> 00:02:42.776 A:middle
simplified layout or tailored to

00:02:42.776 --> 00:02:44.496 A:middle
a subsection of users.

00:02:45.036 --> 00:02:50.716 A:middle
It's about allowing all users to

00:02:50.716 --> 00:02:52.276 A:middle
access the experience that you

00:02:52.276 --> 00:02:52.756 A:middle
created.

00:02:55.976 --> 00:02:57.486 A:middle
So why support VoiceOver?

00:02:58.756 --> 00:03:02.316 A:middle
Well, supporting VoiceOver makes

00:02:58.756 --> 00:03:02.316 A:middle
Well, supporting VoiceOver makes

00:03:02.316 --> 00:03:03.426 A:middle
your app more inclusive.

00:03:05.886 --> 00:03:08.216 A:middle
VoiceOver users are more likely

00:03:08.216 --> 00:03:11.226 A:middle
to choose you app over other

00:03:11.226 --> 00:03:12.686 A:middle
apps that don't support

00:03:12.686 --> 00:03:13.166 A:middle
VoiceOver.

00:03:13.166 --> 00:03:15.716 A:middle
And this is a great community,

00:03:16.496 --> 00:03:17.866 A:middle
so they are more likely to in

00:03:17.866 --> 00:03:20.276 A:middle
turn recommend your app to other

00:03:20.276 --> 00:03:21.346 A:middle
VoiceOver users.

00:03:23.096 --> 00:03:26.286 A:middle
But sadly, for many developers,

00:03:27.266 --> 00:03:28.606 A:middle
those reasons are not enough,

00:03:29.916 --> 00:03:30.516 A:middle
and I get it.

00:03:30.516 --> 00:03:32.196 A:middle
There's only so much time.

00:03:32.196 --> 00:03:33.906 A:middle
There's only so many resources,

00:03:34.956 --> 00:03:36.386 A:middle
and you want to make the best

00:03:36.386 --> 00:03:37.756 A:middle
decisions to create the best

00:03:37.756 --> 00:03:38.816 A:middle
experience for the most of your

00:03:38.816 --> 00:03:39.356 A:middle
users.

00:03:40.766 --> 00:03:42.446 A:middle
So that's why it's so important

00:03:42.446 --> 00:03:44.956 A:middle
today that you realize that

00:03:44.956 --> 00:03:47.476 A:middle
learning VoiceOver can help make

00:03:47.476 --> 00:03:49.086 A:middle
your app more usable for

00:03:49.086 --> 00:03:50.616 A:middle
everyone, not just VoiceOver

00:03:50.616 --> 00:03:52.856 A:middle
users, for all users.

00:03:54.436 --> 00:03:55.986 A:middle
So I bet you're asking yourself,

00:03:55.986 --> 00:03:56.196 A:middle
right?

00:03:56.866 --> 00:03:57.966 A:middle
Can a screen reader do that?

00:03:58.726 --> 00:03:59.926 A:middle
Yeah, absolutely.

00:04:00.056 --> 00:04:01.756 A:middle
I mean look at some of the

00:04:01.956 --> 00:04:03.366 A:middle
latest apps coming out, those

00:04:03.646 --> 00:04:04.416 A:middle
larger texts.

00:04:04.416 --> 00:04:05.386 A:middle
Those cleaner layouts.

00:04:05.386 --> 00:04:07.576 A:middle
They're not just benefiting low

00:04:07.576 --> 00:04:09.596 A:middle
vision users or users with

00:04:09.596 --> 00:04:10.396 A:middle
cognitive needs.

00:04:10.816 --> 00:04:13.236 A:middle
They benefit us all, and the

00:04:13.236 --> 00:04:14.546 A:middle
same is true with VoiceOver.

00:04:15.186 --> 00:04:18.196 A:middle
So here's how VoiceOver could

00:04:18.196 --> 00:04:20.086 A:middle
help you with your app.

00:04:21.586 --> 00:04:23.516 A:middle
Well, testing with VoiceOver can

00:04:23.516 --> 00:04:24.556 A:middle
give you a new perspective.

00:04:25.926 --> 00:04:27.016 A:middle
Now it's easy to take for

00:04:27.016 --> 00:04:29.096 A:middle
granted your app because it's

00:04:29.096 --> 00:04:29.636 A:middle
your app.

00:04:30.196 --> 00:04:31.476 A:middle
You know exactly what it does,

00:04:31.476 --> 00:04:32.446 A:middle
what it's supposed to do, how

00:04:32.446 --> 00:04:33.786 A:middle
it's supposed to do it.

00:04:35.176 --> 00:04:36.346 A:middle
But we take a lot of those

00:04:36.346 --> 00:04:38.596 A:middle
things for granted, and when I

00:04:38.596 --> 00:04:40.376 A:middle
say testing with VoiceOver gives

00:04:40.376 --> 00:04:42.606 A:middle
you a new perspective, it's

00:04:43.266 --> 00:04:44.636 A:middle
getting a chance to experience

00:04:44.636 --> 00:04:45.586 A:middle
your app in a new way.

00:04:46.226 --> 00:04:49.356 A:middle
That's because VoiceOver goes

00:04:49.666 --> 00:04:51.606 A:middle
beyond the way your app location

00:04:51.606 --> 00:04:52.026 A:middle
looks.

00:04:52.156 --> 00:04:54.656 A:middle
I mean an app might look good,

00:04:54.656 --> 00:04:56.136 A:middle
but that doesn't make it usable.

00:04:56.726 --> 00:05:00.136 A:middle
So side-scrolling states, hover

00:04:56.726 --> 00:05:00.136 A:middle
So side-scrolling states, hover

00:05:00.136 --> 00:05:02.366 A:middle
states, they can all give the

00:05:02.366 --> 00:05:04.156 A:middle
allusion of straightforward,

00:05:04.416 --> 00:05:05.846 A:middle
clean, easy-to-use interface.

00:05:07.116 --> 00:05:08.606 A:middle
But testing with VoiceOver goes

00:05:08.606 --> 00:05:11.766 A:middle
beyond that, and so it allows

00:05:11.766 --> 00:05:13.726 A:middle
you to discover new challenges

00:05:13.856 --> 00:05:18.366 A:middle
and insights, and finally, I

00:05:18.366 --> 00:05:19.656 A:middle
believe VoiceOver gets really at

00:05:19.656 --> 00:05:20.646 A:middle
the heart of what we do.

00:05:20.646 --> 00:05:24.526 A:middle
As iOS developers, we pride

00:05:24.526 --> 00:05:25.566 A:middle
ourselves on creating

00:05:26.076 --> 00:05:28.366 A:middle
easy-to-use, easy-to-understand

00:05:28.366 --> 00:05:28.986 A:middle
apps.

00:05:30.166 --> 00:05:33.006 A:middle
Well those values are especially

00:05:33.006 --> 00:05:34.406 A:middle
apparent when using VoiceOver.

00:05:36.116 --> 00:05:39.626 A:middle
So my question to you today is

00:05:39.626 --> 00:05:41.876 A:middle
your app so easy to use you

00:05:41.876 --> 00:05:42.726 A:middle
could use it with your eyes

00:05:42.726 --> 00:05:43.246 A:middle
closed?

00:05:43.736 --> 00:05:46.886 A:middle
And that's not a question just

00:05:46.886 --> 00:05:47.936 A:middle
for testers.

00:05:47.936 --> 00:05:49.906 A:middle
That's a question for designers,

00:05:49.906 --> 00:05:50.546 A:middle
for developers.

00:05:50.806 --> 00:05:53.816 A:middle
Anyone responsible for creating

00:05:53.816 --> 00:05:55.226 A:middle
the best experience possible for

00:05:55.226 --> 00:05:55.866 A:middle
our users.

00:05:56.826 --> 00:05:58.606 A:middle
And the only way to answer that

00:05:58.606 --> 00:06:01.796 A:middle
question is to start testing

00:05:58.606 --> 00:06:01.796 A:middle
question is to start testing

00:06:01.796 --> 00:06:04.216 A:middle
with VoiceOver, and that's what

00:06:04.216 --> 00:06:04.996 A:middle
I'm here for today.

00:06:05.776 --> 00:06:07.596 A:middle
I'm going to give you some ways

00:06:07.596 --> 00:06:08.906 A:middle
of being able to turn on

00:06:08.906 --> 00:06:10.096 A:middle
VoiceOver and start using it.

00:06:10.696 --> 00:06:11.626 A:middle
Figure out where you're at,

00:06:12.166 --> 00:06:14.376 A:middle
where you could improve, and

00:06:14.376 --> 00:06:15.486 A:middle
then I'll give you some things

00:06:15.486 --> 00:06:17.706 A:middle
else to watch out for that might

00:06:17.706 --> 00:06:20.176 A:middle
not only improve your VoiceOver

00:06:20.176 --> 00:06:23.756 A:middle
experience but possibly the

00:06:23.756 --> 00:06:25.296 A:middle
experience that all users get.

00:06:26.726 --> 00:06:28.476 A:middle
And here's where we're going to

00:06:29.036 --> 00:06:29.206 A:middle
start.

00:06:29.366 --> 00:06:30.836 A:middle
We need to know how to use

00:06:30.836 --> 00:06:31.456 A:middle
VoiceOver.

