before my presentation is done.

00:07:00.906 --> 00:07:02.116 A:middle
So how do we turn on VoiceOver?

00:07:02.356 --> 00:07:03.926 A:middle
Well, it starts in settings, and

00:07:03.926 --> 00:07:04.596 A:middle
we go to general.

00:07:05.336 --> 00:07:07.576 A:middle
In general, I can open up the

00:07:07.576 --> 00:07:08.506 A:middle
accessibility menu.

00:07:08.856 --> 00:07:10.396 A:middle
It's a great list of all the

00:07:10.396 --> 00:07:12.136 A:middle
features that we include on our

00:07:12.136 --> 00:07:14.296 A:middle
iOS devices so that we can have

00:07:14.296 --> 00:07:15.756 A:middle
equal access to our users.

00:07:19.406 --> 00:07:20.726 A:middle
And VoiceOver is right at the

00:07:20.726 --> 00:07:22.476 A:middle
top of that list, but I

00:07:22.476 --> 00:07:23.786 A:middle
discourage you from opening it

00:07:23.786 --> 00:07:24.066 A:middle
there.

00:07:24.536 --> 00:07:26.116 A:middle
I discourage you from going in

00:07:26.116 --> 00:07:27.916 A:middle
and enabling VoiceOver because,

00:07:28.026 --> 00:07:29.906 A:middle
again, we might not know enough

00:07:29.906 --> 00:07:31.266 A:middle
about VoiceOver to turn it back

00:07:31.266 --> 00:07:31.676 A:middle
off.

00:07:32.646 --> 00:07:34.016 A:middle
So when I teach people how to

00:07:34.016 --> 00:07:35.116 A:middle
use VoiceOver for the first

00:07:35.116 --> 00:07:37.916 A:middle
time, I encourage you to go to

00:07:37.916 --> 00:07:39.996 A:middle
the bottom of this list to the

00:07:39.996 --> 00:07:41.316 A:middle
accessibility shortcut.

00:07:42.466 --> 00:07:45.866 A:middle
It's here inside of a list of

00:07:45.866 --> 00:07:46.406 A:middle
options.

00:07:46.756 --> 00:07:49.206 A:middle
If I just check VoiceOver, that

00:07:49.206 --> 00:07:50.096 A:middle
means I can easily turn

00:07:50.096 --> 00:07:51.866 A:middle
VoiceOver on when I want to test

00:07:51.866 --> 00:07:54.856 A:middle
it and also turn VoiceOver back

00:07:54.856 --> 00:07:56.406 A:middle
off when I'm not ready to test

00:07:56.406 --> 00:07:58.966 A:middle
it or my phone goes to sleep or

00:07:58.966 --> 00:07:59.656 A:middle
I get a phone.

00:08:00.666 --> 00:08:02.646 A:middle
So just checking VoiceOver in

00:08:02.646 --> 00:08:05.026 A:middle
this box I can turn it on by

00:08:05.026 --> 00:08:06.326 A:middle
triple clicking the home button.

00:08:06.636 --> 00:08:07.296 A:middle
Click, click, click.

00:08:07.296 --> 00:08:09.156 A:middle
And if you have a brand new

00:08:09.156 --> 00:08:10.576 A:middle
device that doesn't have a home

00:08:10.576 --> 00:08:11.966 A:middle
button, well then you'd use the

00:08:12.056 --> 00:08:14.226 A:middle
side button, click, click,

00:08:16.236 --> 00:08:16.376 A:middle
click.

00:08:17.116 --> 00:08:18.866 A:middle
When VoiceOver is enabled, we

00:08:18.866 --> 00:08:20.186 A:middle
see the VoiceOver cursor.

00:08:20.656 --> 00:08:22.586 A:middle
It's a visual reinforcement of

00:08:22.646 --> 00:08:24.306 A:middle
what VoiceOver is trying to

00:08:24.306 --> 00:08:26.316 A:middle
describe, and that's the first

00:08:26.316 --> 00:08:27.406 A:middle
objective when testing

00:08:27.406 --> 00:08:29.366 A:middle
VoiceOver, is to make sure that

00:08:29.366 --> 00:08:32.645 A:middle
these descriptions are accurate

00:08:32.645 --> 00:08:33.275 A:middle
and complete.

00:08:34.456 --> 00:08:35.556 A:middle
And the only way you're going to

00:08:35.556 --> 00:08:37.596 A:middle
test every single element inside

00:08:37.596 --> 00:08:40.515 A:middle
of your app is to navigate with

00:08:40.515 --> 00:08:42.966 A:middle
VoiceOver, and here's how to do

00:08:44.046 --> 00:08:44.116 A:middle
it.

00:08:44.366 --> 00:08:45.696 A:middle
Navigating can be as easy as

00:08:45.696 --> 00:08:46.816 A:middle
just reaching out and touching

00:08:46.816 --> 00:08:47.276 A:middle
the screen.

00:08:48.156 --> 00:08:49.306 A:middle
Dragging your finger across the

00:08:49.306 --> 00:08:50.866 A:middle
screen, VoiceOver will just read

00:08:51.286 --> 00:08:52.306 A:middle
whatever is under your finger.

00:08:52.896 --> 00:08:57.506 A:middle
But that's actually not really

00:08:57.506 --> 00:09:00.156 A:middle
how a lot of people review their

00:08:57.506 --> 00:09:00.156 A:middle
how a lot of people review their

00:09:00.156 --> 00:09:00.506 A:middle
apps.

00:09:01.706 --> 00:09:02.766 A:middle
I start at the top.

00:09:03.046 --> 00:09:04.116 A:middle
I work through everything in

00:09:04.116 --> 00:09:05.346 A:middle
read order to the very end.

00:09:06.436 --> 00:09:08.446 A:middle
VoiceOver users accomplish using

00:09:08.446 --> 00:09:10.626 A:middle
flick navigation, and that's

00:09:10.626 --> 00:09:11.606 A:middle
taking my finger and putting it

00:09:11.606 --> 00:09:13.166 A:middle
on the screen and then flicking

00:09:13.166 --> 00:09:14.536 A:middle
to the right, flicking to the

00:09:14.536 --> 00:09:14.766 A:middle
right.

00:09:15.656 --> 00:09:16.746 A:middle
Now if I went slow enough, it

00:09:16.746 --> 00:09:17.846 A:middle
would just read under my finger,

00:09:17.906 --> 00:09:19.506 A:middle
so you have to really give it a

00:09:19.506 --> 00:09:21.306 A:middle
quick flick until your finger

00:09:21.306 --> 00:09:22.306 A:middle
flies off the screen.

00:09:22.886 --> 00:09:24.316 A:middle
And conversely, I could go back

00:09:24.316 --> 00:09:26.346 A:middle
to the left, and I could go to

00:09:26.346 --> 00:09:27.766 A:middle
the previous item or the next

00:09:27.766 --> 00:09:28.166 A:middle
item.

00:09:28.686 --> 00:09:31.886 A:middle
And it's important that you also

00:09:31.886 --> 00:09:33.236 A:middle
want to keep in mind the

00:09:33.236 --> 00:09:34.766 A:middle
starting position of your

00:09:34.766 --> 00:09:37.066 A:middle
VoiceOver cursor, because if

00:09:37.066 --> 00:09:37.906 A:middle
will start in the middle of your

00:09:37.906 --> 00:09:38.456 A:middle
page.

00:09:39.686 --> 00:09:41.456 A:middle
Well, that would assume as a

00:09:41.456 --> 00:09:43.326 A:middle
user that there isn't anything

00:09:43.326 --> 00:09:45.366 A:middle
before it, and so you might be

00:09:46.216 --> 00:09:47.786 A:middle
leaving your users without all

00:09:48.376 --> 00:09:48.876 A:middle
the story.

00:09:51.116 --> 00:09:53.236 A:middle
So, we have two ways to

00:09:53.236 --> 00:09:56.196 A:middle
navigate, and we have no way to

00:09:56.196 --> 00:09:57.756 A:middle
control how a user navigates.

00:09:58.476 --> 00:10:00.016 A:middle
So you want to test both these

00:09:58.476 --> 00:10:00.016 A:middle
So you want to test both these

00:10:00.016 --> 00:10:01.836 A:middle
ways to make sure they work as

00:10:01.836 --> 00:10:03.506 A:middle
expected in your app.

00:10:05.296 --> 00:10:06.656 A:middle
Now while you're navigating your

00:10:06.656 --> 00:10:08.416 A:middle
app, you may need to pause that

00:10:08.416 --> 00:10:08.806 A:middle
output.

00:10:09.456 --> 00:10:11.086 A:middle
So, if you ever need to have so

00:10:11.086 --> 00:10:13.436 A:middle
stop speaking, just take two

